==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bigotry
<hw>Big"ot*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>bigoterie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of mind of a
bigot; obstinate and unreasoning attachment of one's own belief and
opinions, with narrow-minded intolerance of beliefs opposed to
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The practice or tenets of a bigot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bigram</ent>⟦br⟧
